-- HIGHLIGHTS-ECB's Draghi speaks in European Parliament
-- 
-- Mon Nov 17, 2014 09:24AM EST
-- None



Nov 17 (Reuters) - European Central Bank President Mario Draghi spoke at the European Parliament in Brussels on Monday.

Following are highlights from his comments:  IMPACT OF ECB STEPS SO FAR "We see early indications that our credit-easing package is delivering tangible benefits. Since the beginning of June forward money market rates have shown steep declines across the security spectrum."  ALERT FOR INFLATION RISKS  "We need to remain alert to possible downside risks to our outlook for inflation."  FURTHER ECB MEASURES